<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5630] NullObject is created for a required dependency if the component is removed and added again to the dependency manager</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5630</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a component A with a required dependency to B and C. &lt;br/&gt;
I add A, B and C to the dependency manager. &lt;br/&gt;
Then I remove A and B. &lt;br/&gt;
Finally I only add A again. Now the exception &quot;Could not create null object for class com.example.Activator$B is thrown&quot;. See the attached Activator.&lt;br/&gt;
I did not expect that a NullObject is ever created for a required dependency.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13068379">FELIX-5630</key>
